        "id": "docling_magazine_TheEconomist.2024.03.02_page_075_43",
        "observed_type": "section_header",
        "canon_role": "section_header",
        "text": "A History of the World in 12 Shipwrecks.",
        "bbox": [
          0.6603053440451883,
          0.4796511630017221,
          0.9274809115527767,
          0.4928075396625384
        ],
        "order": 16
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_magazine_TheEconomist.2024.03.02_page_075_44",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "By David Gibbins. St Martin's Press; 304 pages; $32. W&N; £25",
        "bbox": [
          0.6564885520367311,
          0.4927325583505595,
          0.9064885438936533,
          0.5203488371806329
        ],
        "order": 17
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_magazine_TheEconomist.2024.03.02_page_075_45",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Alistice You know hero mister isthe ry of something enormous in an intriguingly specific number of unexpected things. In 2023 alone readers were met with new books about the history of baseball in 50 moments, the West in 14 lives, the information age in five hacks, women in 101 objects and the world in eight plagues, ten dinners or 50 lies. Call it history-bynumbers, or, if you must, the \"histicle\".",
        "bbox": [
          0.6563093673160464,
          0.5319767441852459,
          0.9408396981930844,
          0.6773313493568327
        ],
        "order": 18
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_magazine_TheEconomist.2024.03.02_page_075_11",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Again and again the familiar, bespectacled figure of Mr Sacco pops up in his images. His presence reminds readers that this story is being told through a particular lens-the perspective of a bewildered visitor trying to make sense of it all. He does not pretend to have the answers. He just",
        "bbox": [
          0.3587786292955851,
          0.5334302325514725,
          0.6412213757121686,
          0.6235465113681011
        ],
        "order": 19
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_magazine_TheEconomist.2024.03.02_page_075_7",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "When the issues were first published in the 1990s, readers were mostly uninterested. Now, 30 years later, demand is so high that \"Palestine\" has been out of stock both online and in shops. The publisher, Fantagraphics, says interest surged after October 7th, when Hamas terrorists murdered 1,200 people in Israel. Google searches for the comic book shot up to their highest level since 2004, during the second intifada. As the conflict rages on, the book—a 285page volume collecting all nine issueshas been rushed back into print in America and 11 other countries.",
        "bbox": [
          0.06106870199775493,
          0.5726686506659704,
          0.3416030558028175,
          0.6235465109808359
        ],
        "order": 20
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_magazine_TheEconomist.2024.03.02_page_075_20",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "\"We followed him there... The",
        "bbox": [
          0.44656488790670595,
          0.6468023257816399,
          0.593511443072938,
          0.6569940478302934
        ],
        "order": 22
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_magazine_TheEconomist.2024.03.02_page_075_17",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "\"He was taken to the health",
        "bbox": [
          0.265267175247609,
          0.6482558142566882,
          0.40839694426574985,
          0.6584821429513193
        ],
        "order": 23
      },
      {
        "id": "docling_magazine_TheEconomist.2024.03.02_page_075_13",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "but the neigh-",
        "bbox": [
          0.17366412503222955,
          0.6497093024107579,
          0.24427480803074753,
          0.6599702382244194
        ],
        "order": 24
      }
    ]
